I got a time frame to get

00:04.038 --> 00:04.970
this album done.

00:05.108 --> 00:06.040
Keke takes on too much.

00:06.178 --> 00:07.697
She's having a breakdown.

00:07.835 --> 00:09.009
No, I'm not!

00:10.320 --> 00:11.666
Keke Wyatt's World

00:12.219 --> 00:13.599
A WEtv original

00:13.737 --> 00:15.118
now streaming on ALLBLK.

00:23.057 --> 00:27.613
♪♪

00:28.200 --> 00:35.518
♪♪

00:35.656 --> 00:43.146
♪♪

00:44.630 --> 00:51.741
♪♪

00:51.879 --> 00:58.955
♪♪

00:59.093 --> 01:06.204
♪♪

01:06.342 --> 01:08.689
[Helicopter blades whirring]

01:08.827 --> 01:12.313
♪♪

01:12.451 --> 01:15.972
Nefertiti: We're not leaving.
We're not leaving.

01:16.110 --> 01:22.875
I -- I declare this land, this
hallowed land, as descendants

01:23.013 --> 01:26.224
of the ancestors
of Freedom Lakes.

01:26.362 --> 01:31.919
This land, this hallowed ground,
the autonomous ground of BFM.

01:32.057 --> 01:33.679
Of BFM.

01:33.817 --> 01:36.337
[Crowd chanting "BFM!"]We're not leaving.

01:36.475 --> 01:38.512
[Gunshots]What is it?

01:38.650 --> 01:41.963
It's revolution. What is it?

01:42.102 --> 01:44.690
It's revolution.
What is it?

01:44.828 --> 01:46.313
It's revolution!

01:46.451 --> 01:49.178
[Chanting continues]

01:49.316 --> 01:53.285
♪♪

01:53.423 --> 01:55.805
[Gunshots, dogs barking]

01:55.943 --> 02:02.536
♪♪

02:02.674 --> 02:06.126
Has anybody heard
from Nef?

02:08.024 --> 02:12.062
Run over so many bodies.
A lot of us didn't make it.

02:12.201 --> 02:15.652
I'm trying to go live,
but I'm not getting any signal.

02:15.790 --> 02:18.448
They've cut off
the signal towers.

02:20.105 --> 02:22.452
[Footsteps overhead]

02:24.282 --> 02:26.905
History is
repeating itself.

02:27.043 --> 02:29.149
[Sobbing, dogs barking]

02:29.287 --> 02:37.226
♪♪

02:37.364 --> 02:39.883
[Gunshots, dogs barking]

02:40.021 --> 02:45.889
♪♪

02:46.027 --> 02:48.892
[Sobs]

02:49.030 --> 02:50.653
[Knocking on door]

02:50.791 --> 02:53.759
[Sirens wailing]

02:53.897 --> 02:55.934
[Knocking on door]

02:56.072 --> 03:04.632
♪♪

03:04.770 --> 03:13.193
♪♪

03:13.331 --> 03:14.642
[Gasps]

03:14.780 --> 03:17.127
Well, well. What have we
got here, pretty lady?

03:17.266 --> 03:19.060
[Muffled] Please! No, no!
Please!
Huh?

03:19.199 --> 03:21.649
Please, no, no!What's your name?
What's your name?

03:21.787 --> 03:24.065
No, no!
Please, please.

03:24.204 --> 03:26.654
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

03:26.792 --> 03:28.415
Please, please, please.
I'll do any--

03:28.553 --> 03:31.418
We're not friends,
baby girl.

03:31.556 --> 03:34.179
Oh, no,
not by a long shot.

03:34.317 --> 03:37.493
[Sobbing]

03:37.631 --> 03:39.942
Just getting
this night started.

03:40.081 --> 03:49.367
♪♪

03:49.505 --> 03:58.997
♪♪

03:59.135 --> 04:01.102
[Siren chirps]

04:01.241 --> 04:08.351
♪♪

04:08.489 --> 04:10.526
Male reporter: When it comes
to gun violence in America,

04:10.664 --> 04:12.562
the numbers
are simply staggering.

04:12.700 --> 04:15.013
Female reporter: Chaos erupting
in downtown Atlanta.

04:15.151 --> 04:16.877
Female reporter #2: Police
clashed with protesters,

04:17.015 --> 04:19.224
stopping traffic
and making several arrests.

04:19.362 --> 04:21.399
Female reporter #3: Today marks
the five year anniversary

04:21.536 --> 04:23.021
of the Freeman Lakes explosion,

04:23.159 --> 04:26.024
which claimed the lives
of over 35 people

04:26.162 --> 04:27.922
and dozens more unaccounted for.

04:28.060 --> 04:30.891
The tragedy, which spawned
several conspiracy theories,

04:31.029 --> 04:33.549
including the notion
that authorities intentionally

04:33.687 --> 04:35.999
bombed the apartment complex
while tenants

04:36.137 --> 04:37.691
were still on the grounds.

04:37.829 --> 04:40.245
Investigators later concluded
that the explosion

04:40.383 --> 04:42.074
was a result of faulty wiring,

04:42.212 --> 04:44.698
which caused a boiler explosion
on the ground,

04:44.836 --> 04:47.563
likely the result of tampering
from the now-defunct

04:47.701 --> 04:49.634
radical terrorist group, BFM,

04:49.772 --> 04:51.532
who were squatting
on the property

04:51.670 --> 04:54.397
after a government evacuation
was ordered.

04:54.534 --> 04:57.055
In the past, many conspiracy
theorists have alleged

04:57.193 --> 05:00.748
that the Freeman Lake fires
was in fact a civilian attack

05:00.886 --> 05:02.647
on US soil by authorities.

05:02.785 --> 05:07.479
Sarah! Jacob! Let's go.
I don't want to be late.

05:07.617 --> 05:09.309
Noting that the attack
was nothing more

05:09.447 --> 05:11.103
than a modern day purge.

05:11.241 --> 05:13.105
Jacob: Hey, Mom.
I'm ready.
Hey, baby.

05:13.243 --> 05:14.831
The Senate committee
later concluded

05:14.969 --> 05:16.419
that there was
no sufficient evidence

05:16.557 --> 05:18.248
to support those claims.

05:18.387 --> 05:21.079
[Sighs] Sarah!
Let's go, honey.

05:21.217 --> 05:23.461
Shortly after
the Freeman Lakes fire,

05:23.599 --> 05:25.808
the eccentric real estate
magnate Charles Marshall

05:25.946 --> 05:28.949
purchased the land
and conducted a full demolition

05:29.087 --> 05:31.848
of the apartment complex
and transformed the grounds

05:31.986 --> 05:35.369
into a sprawling lake house
resort for the rich and famous.

05:35.507 --> 05:37.475
Tonight, the billionaire
developer hosts

05:37.613 --> 05:40.167
his third annual gala,
which has become a staple

05:40.305 --> 05:42.687
for the elite here
in the metropolitan area.

05:42.825 --> 05:44.551
The event is known
for its risque

05:44.689 --> 05:47.416
and provocative performances.

05:47.554 --> 05:50.867
[Exhales deeply]

05:51.005 --> 05:54.837
♪♪

05:59.393 --> 06:01.361
Um...

06:03.432 --> 06:07.850
I know that this year
anniversary marks a moment

06:07.988 --> 06:11.129
in our lives that we will
never forget.

06:11.267 --> 06:17.031
It's something that will remain
etched in our conscious,

06:17.169 --> 06:20.380
our hearts forever.

06:20.518 --> 06:22.589
And, unfortunately,

06:22.727 --> 06:25.315
trauma has played a key part
in our history,

06:25.454 --> 06:29.975
but healing will come.

06:30.113 --> 06:32.081
Slowly.

06:32.219 --> 06:34.186
So, as we get through
this day --

06:34.324 --> 06:35.981
Ms. Duvernay?
Yeah.

06:36.119 --> 06:37.949
If it's all right
with you,

06:38.087 --> 06:42.712
I really don't want to talk
about the shooting today.

06:42.850 --> 06:47.130
Last year's shooting was
a horrible event,

06:47.268 --> 06:49.339
so...

06:49.478 --> 06:50.686
how about this?

06:50.824 --> 06:52.722
How about we go
around the room

06:52.860 --> 06:55.829
and just share a few words
of positivity?

06:55.967 --> 06:59.798
It can be about anything
that you want.

07:07.944 --> 07:09.394
Okay.

07:09.532 --> 07:11.361
Um...

07:11.500 --> 07:13.571
Purpose.

07:13.709 --> 07:15.538
How about purpose?

07:15.676 --> 07:19.611
I know that today is your last
day before your summer vacation,

07:19.749 --> 07:22.200
so I want to remind
all of you

07:22.338 --> 07:27.343
that each and every one
of you have a purpose.

07:27.481 --> 07:29.069
By no means are you here
by accident,

07:29.207 --> 07:32.348
so I always want you
to remember that

07:32.486 --> 07:34.419
and never take it for granted.

07:34.557 --> 07:37.974
The truth is that everyone here
is going through change.

07:38.112 --> 07:41.668
Huge transformational change.

07:41.806 --> 07:43.980
And you can view it
as good or bad.

07:44.118 --> 07:49.917
You have the choice --
not just today, but every day --

07:50.055 --> 07:52.989
to see the good.

07:53.127 --> 07:55.095
Okay?

07:55.233 --> 07:56.476
Purpose.

07:56.614 --> 07:59.271
[Bell rings]

08:01.895 --> 08:06.416
Well, I'll see you all
in a few months.

08:06.555 --> 08:09.558
Have a purposeful summer.

08:09.696 --> 08:12.492
Purpose. Purpose.
Purpose.

08:12.630 --> 08:14.804
Right?

08:16.530 --> 08:18.808
Purpose.

08:26.575 --> 08:29.578
[Cell phone buzzing]

08:34.789 --> 08:36.861
-Hello?
-Yes, Ms. Janice Duvernay?

08:36.999 --> 08:39.173
This is a collections
call from --

08:39.311 --> 08:41.140
Oh, my God.

08:41.279 --> 08:42.693
[Knock on door]

08:42.832 --> 08:44.351
[Sighing] Yes?

08:44.489 --> 08:46.940
Hey.
Hey. Sorry.

08:47.078 --> 08:48.665
[Chuckles]
Sorry.

08:48.804 --> 08:52.601
Just coming to check on you.
How you holding up?

08:52.739 --> 08:55.327
I'm pushing through.

08:55.465 --> 08:57.467
Any plans for the summer?

08:57.606 --> 08:59.987
They're all work.[Laughs]

09:00.125 --> 09:03.232
I need a job.
I need money.

09:03.370 --> 09:04.751
Yeah.

09:04.889 --> 09:06.856
All right, guys.
Some fun trivia for you

09:06.994 --> 09:09.721
to take home to your parents.

09:09.859 --> 09:12.206
This gentleman right here
with the incredible goatee

09:12.344 --> 09:15.589
founded Chicago.

09:15.727 --> 09:17.453
It's huge.

09:17.591 --> 09:20.939
Jean Baptiste Point du Sable.

09:21.077 --> 09:24.494
Try saying that 10 times.

09:24.633 --> 09:26.669
Is that not exciting
for you guys?

09:26.807 --> 09:29.051
I mean,
a Black man founded Chicago.

09:29.189 --> 09:32.675
I mean, we in Augusta, bro.
What I got to do with us?

09:32.813 --> 09:37.128
Okay, valid question.

09:37.266 --> 09:41.546
If you go into places
and you don't know your truth

09:41.684 --> 09:43.824
or your history,
it leaves you vulnerable

09:43.962 --> 09:46.827
to whatever people say
or do to you.

09:46.965 --> 09:48.967
You already got
your woke card, bro.

09:49.105 --> 09:51.038
You don't got
to keep pushing.

09:51.176 --> 09:52.246
[Laughter]

09:52.384 --> 09:54.663
All right.
Fair enough.

09:54.801 --> 09:58.218
But, listen,
this ain't about me, okay?

09:58.356 --> 10:01.566
Yes. I love teaching
this history stuff.

10:01.704 --> 10:04.120
I do.

10:04.258 --> 10:06.882
But it's easy to forget that,
with everything

10:07.020 --> 10:11.818
you've been through,
especially this past year,

10:11.956 --> 10:15.718
the world can still blame you
and dismiss you.

10:15.856 --> 10:17.824
I have deep admiration
for what Black people

10:17.962 --> 10:20.585
have contributed
to this country.

10:20.723 --> 10:23.243
This civilization.

10:23.381 --> 10:26.556
Speaking of, I've decided
to just give you guys two books

10:26.695 --> 10:28.455
for your summer reading.

10:28.593 --> 10:30.940
[Chuckles]

10:31.078 --> 10:34.047
Listen, you're going to love
these books, all right?

10:34.185 --> 10:35.738
"They Came Before Columbus"

10:35.876 --> 10:37.982
and "In Search of
the Racial Frontier:

10:38.120 --> 10:42.227
African Americans in
the American West 1528-1990."

10:42.365 --> 10:45.023
I know, it's a mouthful,
but I'm gonna e-mail you

10:45.161 --> 10:46.369
some links so you know
how to find them.

10:46.507 --> 10:49.476
And they haven't been
banned...yet.

10:49.614 --> 10:51.823
So you should be able
to find them at the library.

10:51.961 --> 10:53.342
[Bell rings]

10:53.480 --> 10:55.033
All right, guys,
thank you for a great year.

10:55.171 --> 10:59.141
Have a safe,
great, and productive summer.

10:59.279 --> 11:01.281
I --

11:03.283 --> 11:05.388
[Jazz piano playing on radio]

11:05.526 --> 11:10.566
♪♪

11:10.704 --> 11:15.709
♪♪

11:15.847 --> 11:19.057
[Humming]

11:19.195 --> 11:23.441
♪♪

11:23.579 --> 11:26.444
[Cell phone rings]

11:26.582 --> 11:28.342
[Music stops]

11:28.480 --> 11:32.761
Sarah: Hey, Mom, is there any
way I can go to Raven's house?

11:32.899 --> 11:35.142
You were just there, Sarah.
No.

11:35.280 --> 11:36.834
I'm on my way
to pick up Jacob.

11:36.972 --> 11:38.352
Just get a ride home --

11:38.490 --> 11:39.871
Don't say it. Ugh.

11:40.009 --> 11:41.908
[Cell phone beeps]

11:42.046 --> 11:45.221
Save me, Jesus,
from these children.

11:45.359 --> 11:48.466
[Music resumes]

11:48.604 --> 11:50.606
[Cell phone rings]

11:50.744 --> 11:52.194
[Music stops]

11:52.332 --> 11:55.404
This better be an apology
for hanging up on me.

11:55.542 --> 11:57.302
Man: Ms. Duvernay?

11:57.440 --> 12:00.961
Wow.
You guys are truly relentless.

12:01.099 --> 12:02.549
Mrs. Janice Duvernay?

12:02.687 --> 12:04.516
Yes, it's me. I know, I know.

12:04.654 --> 12:05.863
This call is being recorded.

12:06.001 --> 12:08.175
This is an attempt
to collect a debt.

12:08.313 --> 12:11.558
Ms. Duvernay, I can assure you
I am not a bill collector.

12:11.696 --> 12:13.491
My name is Lionel Dessalines,

12:13.629 --> 12:16.356
and I'm calling on behalf
of your grandfather,

12:16.494 --> 12:18.668
the late, great
Bishop Papa Dean.

12:18.807 --> 12:20.947
My grandfather?

12:21.085 --> 12:24.157
Yes. Bishop Dean
recently transitioned,

12:24.295 --> 12:26.228
and I'm the executor
of his estate.

12:26.366 --> 12:28.264
I'm afraid it's urgent
that we meet at once.

12:28.402 --> 12:29.541
Wait.

12:29.679 --> 12:31.854
I haven't seen
or spoken to my grandfather

12:31.992 --> 12:33.787
since I was a little girl.

12:33.925 --> 12:35.858
He and my mother were estranged.

12:35.996 --> 12:37.239
Nonetheless...

12:37.377 --> 12:40.380
you are the sole heir
to his estate.

12:40.518 --> 12:42.520
You and your children.
Now I need to --

12:42.658 --> 12:45.143
Hold up.
How did you get this number?

12:45.281 --> 12:46.835
See, I don't have
time for scams.

12:46.973 --> 12:48.802
Let me guess.
You're some African prince.

12:48.940 --> 12:50.597
And if I give you
my bank information

12:50.735 --> 12:52.357
and let you withdraw a few
hundred dollars

12:52.495 --> 12:54.497
on good faith,
you will release some funds

12:54.635 --> 12:57.466
from some secret account
held by a foreign government.

12:57.604 --> 12:59.054
Is that how that works?

12:59.192 --> 13:03.403
Yeah. Not today, Prince Joaquin.
Not today, Satan.

13:03.541 --> 13:05.267
[Cell phone beeps]

13:05.405 --> 13:12.757
♪♪

13:12.895 --> 13:20.592
♪♪

13:23.768 --> 13:25.839
[Sighs]

13:40.889 --> 13:44.030
Okay.

13:49.345 --> 13:52.072
[Sighs]

13:52.210 --> 13:54.247
[Exhales sharply]

13:56.559 --> 13:58.113
Mm.

14:00.046 --> 14:01.771
Hey, baby, I'm home.

14:01.910 --> 14:04.533
Hey.
Hey.

14:04.671 --> 14:06.224
The last day of school.

14:06.362 --> 14:08.951
I see we're
celebrating already.

14:09.089 --> 14:12.299
[Chuckles] Well, I am.

14:12.437 --> 14:14.163
I had to get
a glass of wine

14:14.301 --> 14:16.407
so I could go
through these bills.

14:16.545 --> 14:19.479
Babe, I cannot seem
to catch up.

14:19.617 --> 14:21.343
But I did catch
Principal Hall today,

14:21.481 --> 14:23.759
and I will be teaching
summer school.

14:23.897 --> 14:25.105
We could use the money.

14:25.243 --> 14:27.176
Baby, if you just
let me chip in more.

14:27.314 --> 14:30.179
No, I don't need you
to chip in more

14:30.317 --> 14:32.457
on my late husband's
medical bills, okay?

14:32.595 --> 14:34.632
It's enough
that you're in his house.

14:34.770 --> 14:37.152
Wait, where's Sarah?Oh, sh--

14:37.290 --> 14:39.913
-Come on. Okay. Come on.
-Hey, Ms. Duvernay.

14:40.051 --> 14:42.053
Mr. Cheeto.

14:42.191 --> 14:44.884
Hello, uh, Raven.
Sarah!

14:45.022 --> 14:46.816
Sarah: Uh, Ben said
it was cool.

14:46.955 --> 14:49.095
Cool?

14:49.233 --> 14:51.097
I think I know
what might have happened.

14:51.235 --> 14:53.099
You just told her yes?

14:53.237 --> 14:55.273
Without thinking
to double check with me?

14:55.411 --> 14:59.208
Um, maybe because I thought
she wouldn't have asked me

14:59.346 --> 15:00.865
after she'd already
asked you.

15:01.003 --> 15:02.246
Okay, well, just --

15:02.384 --> 15:04.627
just always ask first,
okay, Ben?

15:04.765 --> 15:06.526
Um...
Am I not

15:06.664 --> 15:09.115
a decision-making adult in this
household, as well?

15:09.253 --> 15:12.601
You are.
But not when it comes to...

15:14.879 --> 15:17.399
What I mean, baby,

15:17.537 --> 15:20.850
we cannot let the kids play us
against each other.

15:20.989 --> 15:22.887
And in order to have
a united front,

15:23.025 --> 15:24.993
we have got to communicate.

15:25.131 --> 15:26.995
We are the adults.

15:27.133 --> 15:28.582
Okay.
Yeah.

15:28.720 --> 15:30.930
We'll talk to her
as soon as Raven leaves.

15:31.068 --> 15:32.862
Mm-hmm.

15:33.001 --> 15:34.140
I get it. Okay?

15:34.278 --> 15:36.936
No good cop, bad cop.

15:37.074 --> 15:39.110
I'm with you on this.
Mm-hmm.

15:39.248 --> 15:41.664
And I'm going to make
a really delicious dinner.

15:41.802 --> 15:42.942
Yeah, go.
Yes.

15:43.080 --> 15:44.702
Go.

15:44.840 --> 15:46.946
[Sighs]

15:48.809 --> 15:57.542
♪♪

15:57.680 --> 16:06.379
♪♪

16:06.517 --> 16:15.422
♪♪

16:17.631 --> 16:19.564
Mm.

16:25.398 --> 16:29.712
Mr. Cheeto, this jerk chicken --
out of this world.

16:29.850 --> 16:30.990
[Chuckles]

16:31.128 --> 16:33.199
It was so good.

16:33.337 --> 16:36.236
I mean, it's one thing
to teach Black history.

16:36.374 --> 16:37.858
But where you learn
how to cook Black?

16:37.997 --> 16:39.584
Oh, my gosh.

16:39.722 --> 16:41.345
I mean,
everything was seasoned.

16:41.483 --> 16:42.829
It ain't had
no raisins in it.

16:42.967 --> 16:44.141
Oh, yeah.
We don't do raisins.

16:44.279 --> 16:46.453
Okay. Okay, Ray.

16:46.591 --> 16:48.214
You know, you don't have
to kiss up to him anymore.

16:48.352 --> 16:49.905
He's not your teacher.
School's out.

16:50.043 --> 16:52.494
All right, kids,
let's just clear the table.

16:52.632 --> 16:55.255
-You, too, Raven.
-Hey, She is a guest.

16:55.393 --> 16:57.464
No, she's not.
She's always here.

16:57.602 --> 16:59.742
Hey, shut up.
You're fine.

16:59.880 --> 17:01.089
I'm-a go.

17:01.227 --> 17:03.194
Right.
Thanks for dinner.

17:03.332 --> 17:04.816
You're welcome, baby.
And please tell your mom

17:04.954 --> 17:07.026
I said we need to meet soon
for a minute.
Yeah.

17:07.164 --> 17:08.751
Hey, and text me
when you make it home.

17:08.888 --> 17:09.959
Seriously.

17:10.098 --> 17:13.066
[Ringing]

17:13.204 --> 17:14.412
Oh, I'll get it.

17:14.550 --> 17:16.137
No.
Um, I'll get it.

17:16.276 --> 17:18.589
You finish your chores.

17:24.250 --> 17:26.045
-Hello.
-Ms. Duvernay.

17:26.183 --> 17:27.598
Please don't hang up.

17:27.736 --> 17:29.703
Who is this? And how did you
get my home number?

17:29.841 --> 17:31.291
Nobody calls this number.

17:31.429 --> 17:33.638
There's a courier at
your door with a letter.

17:33.776 --> 17:36.641
Sign for it.
Take it. Read it.

17:36.779 --> 17:39.092
[Gasps] I'll be in touch in a few days.

17:39.230 --> 17:40.542
[Busy signal]

17:40.680 --> 17:44.546
Ms. Janice,
there's a dude at your door.

17:44.684 --> 17:48.446
♪♪

18:04.669 --> 18:07.016
Y'all are
getting evicted?

18:07.155 --> 18:08.501
Uh --
What?

18:08.639 --> 18:10.572
Raven, let us know
when you get home.

18:10.710 --> 18:12.505
Okay.

18:20.202 --> 18:21.617
Ben: What is it, babe?

18:21.755 --> 18:24.862
Yeah.
What does the letter say, Mom?

18:25.000 --> 18:28.245
That my grandfather died.

18:28.383 --> 18:32.456
It says there's a will and that
I'm the main beneficiary.

18:32.594 --> 18:35.114
Jacob:
What does that mean?

18:35.252 --> 18:38.531
It means that
we're going to be rich.

18:38.669 --> 18:40.533
And I'm finally
getting my Tesla.

18:40.671 --> 18:42.362
For real?
We're going to be rich, Mom?

18:42.500 --> 18:44.433
Baby, calm down.
I don't know anything.

18:44.571 --> 18:47.988
It says I'll be contacted
in a few days.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.094
You okay?

18:50.232 --> 18:52.476
♪♪

18:52.614 --> 18:56.135
Just go finish your chores,
guys, please.

18:56.273 --> 18:58.206
Should I get my red
interior or white?

18:58.344 --> 19:00.760
You're not getting a Tesla.Come on, bro.

19:02.451 --> 19:05.178
You know, I got a call
about that will thing today,

19:05.316 --> 19:07.387
and I thought it was a scam.

19:07.525 --> 19:09.769
I guess it was real.

19:09.907 --> 19:12.737
I have never heard you talk
about your grandfather.

19:12.875 --> 19:16.776
Because I barely knew him.
My mother was an only child,

19:16.914 --> 19:18.743
and they had
a strained relationship.

19:18.881 --> 19:21.746
She didn't agree
with a lot of his beliefs

19:21.884 --> 19:25.233
and didn't think that
we were safe with him.

19:26.855 --> 19:30.859
Homey, this could be
the answer to so many things.

19:30.997 --> 19:33.033
What? I mean, maybe now you
don't have to take

19:33.172 --> 19:34.759
that summer job.

19:34.897 --> 19:38.107
Everybody is counting money
we don't even know exists yet.

19:38.246 --> 19:40.109
I want it on the record
that I asked you

19:40.248 --> 19:41.939
to marry me twice...[Scoffs]

19:42.077 --> 19:44.597
...before you became an heiress.
So next time I ask you,

19:44.735 --> 19:46.461
it won't be because
of you money.

19:46.599 --> 19:47.841
Mm.

19:47.979 --> 19:51.466
We might actually have the space
to plan our future.

19:51.604 --> 19:54.538
My future is taking this
summer teaching job

19:54.676 --> 19:57.644
and trying to get from
under these bills.

19:59.370 --> 20:02.304
So you're just going to dodge
the part about you and me?

20:02.442 --> 20:04.341
Our future?

20:04.479 --> 20:08.207
The future between me and you,
that future?

20:08.345 --> 20:11.831
I'm not comfortable yet.

20:11.969 --> 20:15.662
When are you going
to get comfortable?

20:15.800 --> 20:18.872
Baby, Bryce, he's been gone
for four years,

20:19.010 --> 20:22.842
but it's like he's still here
in the bedroom with us.

20:22.980 --> 20:24.257
The kids --

20:24.395 --> 20:26.708
Need time to adjust, right.
I-I know.

20:26.846 --> 20:30.332
You can't keep using
that as an excuse.

20:30.470 --> 20:33.818
I've been living here for,
what, almost a year?

20:33.956 --> 20:37.995
Okay, and they are adjusted
as they're going to get.

20:38.133 --> 20:39.583
And I know I joke a lot

20:39.721 --> 20:42.206
so you don't think
I'm being serious.

20:42.344 --> 20:44.243
Those are jokes?

20:44.381 --> 20:46.106
You're not very funny.

20:46.245 --> 20:48.937
♪♪

20:49.075 --> 20:51.353
Okay, well...

20:51.491 --> 20:54.287
you can't keep
avoiding this.

20:54.425 --> 20:56.220
It's not fair,
Janice.

20:56.358 --> 21:03.779
♪♪

21:03.917 --> 21:11.200
♪♪

21:11.339 --> 21:13.272
[Dance music plays]

21:13.410 --> 21:20.969
♪♪

21:21.107 --> 21:28.666
♪♪

21:28.804 --> 21:36.156
♪♪

21:36.295 --> 21:43.854
♪♪

21:43.992 --> 21:47.133
Man: Whoa!

21:47.271 --> 21:48.893
Good evening, ladies and gents.

21:49.031 --> 21:53.139
I'm DJ Dolo,
your resident DJ at Lake Levi.

21:53.277 --> 21:54.899
Tonight, I'll be
entertaining you

21:55.037 --> 21:59.387
with the soul classics of the
'80s, '90s, 2000, and beyond.

21:59.525 --> 22:02.113
A word, sir.

22:02.251 --> 22:05.220
Shortly, we'll be starting
our classic costume

22:05.358 --> 22:08.672
and scene reenactment where
the grand prize winner

22:08.810 --> 22:14.194
will win $50,000 for best
costume and scene reenactment

22:14.333 --> 22:17.819
from an iconic horror movie.

22:17.957 --> 22:19.234
Let's get it.

22:19.372 --> 22:21.443
[Rap music plays]

22:21.581 --> 22:30.935
♪♪

22:31.073 --> 22:40.082
♪♪

22:40.220 --> 22:42.499
Okay, Thomas,
what was so important

22:42.637 --> 22:46.951
that it warranted pulling me
away from my esteemed guests?

22:47.089 --> 22:48.884
We have a problem, sir.

22:49.022 --> 22:51.335
Someone within the staff
has been...

22:51.473 --> 22:53.061
How should I put it?

22:53.199 --> 22:56.375
Someone has been poking
and probing around

22:56.513 --> 22:58.653
and asking an awful
lot of questions.

22:58.791 --> 23:02.415
Okay. And who might
this individual be?

23:02.553 --> 23:06.626
A Gerald DuBois, sir.
Supposedly a journalist.

23:06.764 --> 23:09.180
Some sort of
a documentary filmmaker.

23:09.318 --> 23:10.837
Ah.

23:10.975 --> 23:13.219
He claims to have proof and
knowledge that the government

23:13.357 --> 23:17.465
ordered a top secret excavation
on these grounds

23:17.603 --> 23:20.468
after the Freeman Lake
bombing.

23:20.606 --> 23:23.505
Okay, proceed.

23:23.643 --> 23:25.576
This excavation resulted

23:25.714 --> 23:29.442
in the finding
of several skeletal remains.

23:29.580 --> 23:30.961
Is that so?

23:31.099 --> 23:36.173
Yes, sir. Remains that date
back over 200 years.

23:36.311 --> 23:39.659
Remains of the original
community members

23:39.797 --> 23:41.143
of Freeman Lake.

23:41.281 --> 23:45.009
Now, what would
give him that idea?

23:45.147 --> 23:47.943
Put his information
on my desk.

23:48.081 --> 23:51.015
But, sir, we --It's buried, Tom.

23:51.153 --> 23:52.638
Literally.

23:52.776 --> 23:54.709
Long before
you took your first step

23:54.847 --> 23:56.987
on this planet Earth.

23:57.125 --> 23:59.921
Hell, long before I did.

24:00.059 --> 24:02.648
There are people in high places,
my forefathers,

24:02.786 --> 24:04.235
who have gone
to great lengths

24:04.373 --> 24:06.099
to ensure that much
of this country's history

24:06.237 --> 24:10.241
is omitted and shielded
from the common man.

24:10.379 --> 24:12.174
[Chuckles]

24:12.312 --> 24:14.694
Perhaps you're right.

24:14.832 --> 24:18.664
My ancestors have
honorably served your ancestors

24:18.802 --> 24:21.045
for generations.

24:21.183 --> 24:23.945
Centuries even.

24:24.083 --> 24:27.569
I would hate to be the Freeman
to drop the ball

24:27.707 --> 24:32.816
during my watch,
but what rattled me most

24:32.954 --> 24:35.508
is when he mentioned
he had further proof

24:35.646 --> 24:41.825
that a secret society known
as The System actually exists

24:41.963 --> 24:47.416
and their alleged rituals
are very true.

24:47.555 --> 24:51.075
♪♪

24:51.213 --> 24:53.699
I'll leave you
to your devices.

24:56.564 --> 24:57.772
Should I --

24:57.910 --> 25:00.015
Proceed
with tonight's ritual.

25:00.153 --> 25:05.365
♪♪

25:05.504 --> 25:10.716
♪♪

25:10.854 --> 25:13.132
Okay, everyone,
it's about that time.

25:13.270 --> 25:16.066
We're going to get the show
started right now.

25:16.204 --> 25:17.481
Our first contest --

25:17.619 --> 25:20.035
[Screaming]

25:20.173 --> 25:24.626
♪♪

25:24.764 --> 25:27.491
Please save me!
Somebody save me!

25:27.629 --> 25:29.010
They're gonna kill me!

25:29.148 --> 25:31.150
"Friday the 13th Part VII:
New Blood"?

25:31.288 --> 25:32.358
Please help!

25:32.496 --> 25:34.636
[Scythe slices, crowd screams]

25:34.774 --> 25:39.089
♪♪

26:03.562 --> 26:05.115
[Exhales deeply]

26:32.970 --> 26:35.352
[Cell phone buzzes]

26:35.490 --> 26:37.423
Mm. Morning!

26:37.561 --> 26:39.667
Good morning, Ri.

26:39.805 --> 26:42.083
Good morning, beautiful.

26:42.221 --> 26:43.740
[Laughs]

26:43.878 --> 26:45.707
Look, girl,
I know it's last minute,

26:45.845 --> 26:48.296
but are you down for brunch
at Test Kitchen?

26:48.434 --> 26:51.333
Me? Brunch? Ha!
Yes. That is simple math.

26:51.471 --> 26:54.198
Wait a minute. Doesn't summer
school start today?

26:54.336 --> 26:56.718
Yes, but there's been
a change of plans.

26:56.856 --> 26:58.409
I talked to Principal Hall
this morning.

26:58.547 --> 27:01.550
Look, I will tell you everything
when I see you.

27:01.689 --> 27:03.898
All right. Okay.
Well, maybe we can

27:04.036 --> 27:06.659
make this our
little routine for the summer.

27:06.797 --> 27:10.283
You know, a little Mimosa
Mondays a No-no Freaky Friday.

27:10.421 --> 27:13.010
Okay, maybe
to be determined?

27:13.148 --> 27:15.357
Okay. Okay.
All right, I'll get ready

27:15.495 --> 27:17.946
because I am starving.

27:18.084 --> 27:19.810
Please don't take too long.

27:19.948 --> 27:21.260
-I won't.
-You sure?

27:21.398 --> 27:24.435
-I won't. I promise.
-Okay, girl. Bye!

27:24.573 --> 27:30.441
♪♪

27:30.579 --> 27:31.684
Hey.

27:31.822 --> 27:33.686
[Chuckles] You are crazy.

27:33.824 --> 27:35.136
Mm!

27:35.274 --> 27:36.413
Mm!

27:36.551 --> 27:38.277
Now, why can't
an African prince call me?

27:38.415 --> 27:41.487
I want to go to Zamunda.Zamunda, Ri?

27:41.625 --> 27:44.317
It's in Atlanta.

27:44.455 --> 27:46.526
Please, the only thing
my family passed down

27:46.665 --> 27:49.288
is diabetes and bad checks.

27:49.426 --> 27:50.738
[Laughs]

27:50.876 --> 27:54.362
All jokes aside,
I'm so happy for you.

27:54.500 --> 27:56.364
And I know the kids
must be on cloud nine.

27:56.502 --> 27:57.779
Oh, my goodness.

27:57.917 --> 27:59.367
The kids think Christmas
came early this year.

27:59.505 --> 28:02.750
I am trying to manage
their expectations.

28:02.888 --> 28:05.269
I mean,
I hardly knew Papa Dean,

28:05.407 --> 28:07.547
and we still haven't sat down
with the estate planners,

28:07.686 --> 28:10.274
so not all
that glitters is gold.

28:10.412 --> 28:11.897
Okay?

28:13.622 --> 28:15.901
What about Ben?

28:17.903 --> 28:21.389
Ben is even more uncertain.
I've just...

28:21.527 --> 28:25.013
I've been keeping him
close yet at bay for so long.

28:25.151 --> 28:29.466
Mm-hmm, yeah, like turning down
his two proposals now?

28:29.604 --> 28:31.571
Okay, Ri.
What?

28:31.710 --> 28:33.125
It's true.

28:33.263 --> 28:35.852
It's true.
It's -- It --

28:35.990 --> 28:37.992
It wastrue.

28:38.130 --> 28:39.925
But I'm tired of playing
cat and mouse.

28:40.063 --> 28:42.065
I never even
really intended to.

28:42.203 --> 28:44.688
It's just that,
when we lost Bryce, I...

28:44.826 --> 28:46.759
Oh. Mnh-mnh.

28:46.897 --> 28:49.141
Okay. Okay.

28:51.039 --> 28:52.972
It's okay.

28:53.110 --> 28:54.560
I just -- I --

28:54.698 --> 28:58.460
I couldn't fathom
sharing my space with anyone,

28:58.598 --> 29:00.531
let alone my entire life.

29:00.669 --> 29:03.051
And Ben shows up for me.

29:03.189 --> 29:07.366
And he shows up for the kids,
and I value that.

29:07.504 --> 29:09.678
I value him.

29:09.817 --> 29:13.165
So I've had
to remind myself that...

29:13.303 --> 29:17.100
Bryce would want us
to be happy again.

29:17.238 --> 29:22.070
I think I'm finally open
to receiving

29:22.208 --> 29:24.624
all that
I'm deserving of.

29:24.763 --> 29:28.525
Absolutely. And I love
and fully support that.

29:28.663 --> 29:33.979
So, now, with this newfound
fortune and love

29:34.117 --> 29:37.741
and fame,
brunch is on you, right?

29:37.879 --> 29:40.606
[Giggles]

29:40.744 --> 29:43.505
What is wrong with you?Come on.

29:43.643 --> 29:46.715
Cheers to you.
[Laughs]

29:46.854 --> 29:48.925
You are funny.

29:52.998 --> 29:56.691
Hey.
What you doing?

29:56.829 --> 30:00.108
Ah, I was just getting books
for my summer reading list.

30:00.246 --> 30:03.215
I found one -- "March"
by Congressman John Lewis.

30:03.353 --> 30:07.012
It's got illustrations and
it's almost like a comic book.

30:07.150 --> 30:09.359
I really think Jacob's
going to like it.

30:09.497 --> 30:12.983
Baby, you know I love the way
you think about my kids.

30:13.121 --> 30:14.916
I'm trying to find one
for Sarah.

30:15.054 --> 30:16.331
There's a lot
of great YA novels,

30:16.469 --> 30:19.162
but she's a tougher
nut to crack.

30:20.819 --> 30:23.166
How was brunch?

30:23.304 --> 30:24.546
Ben...

30:24.684 --> 30:26.100
ask me again.

30:26.238 --> 30:29.413
How was brunch?
[Chuckles]

30:29.551 --> 30:31.277
The question.

30:31.415 --> 30:34.211
The one you've asked
twice already.

30:34.349 --> 30:37.076
♪♪

30:37.214 --> 30:38.733
Are you serious?

30:38.871 --> 30:40.873
Right now?
Mm-hmm.

30:41.011 --> 30:43.565
Y-Yeah. Okay.

30:43.703 --> 30:44.912
I...

30:45.050 --> 30:47.500
Wait. Um, don't move.

30:47.638 --> 30:49.502
It's, uh...

30:49.640 --> 30:57.683
♪♪

30:57.821 --> 30:59.167
[Laughs]

30:59.305 --> 31:00.997
No, no, no. Shit.

31:01.135 --> 31:02.930
Hold on, baby.

31:04.863 --> 31:06.381
Uh, top --
top drawer of the --

31:06.519 --> 31:08.418
Oh, my God. Yes!

31:08.556 --> 31:11.283
♪♪

31:11.421 --> 31:13.561
[Laughs]

31:13.699 --> 31:14.942
Um...

31:15.080 --> 31:17.496
You are the one
I've been waiting for.

31:19.291 --> 31:21.500
No matter what life
throws at you,

31:21.638 --> 31:24.192
as long as
I'm on this Earth,

31:24.330 --> 31:27.644
you won't have
to do it alone.

31:27.782 --> 31:31.130
I promise to be the soft place
that you fall.

31:31.268 --> 31:35.997
And I promise to be the hard-ass
that challenges you

31:36.135 --> 31:38.966
whenever you need
to be challenged.

31:39.104 --> 31:41.830
Because, baby,
you deserve to be loved.

31:41.969 --> 31:45.558
You deserve
to be cherished.

31:45.696 --> 31:48.596
I love you. I want you.

31:48.734 --> 31:50.736
I need you.
[Laughs]

31:50.874 --> 31:53.635
Forever and ever.

31:53.773 --> 31:55.672
Will you marry me?

31:55.810 --> 31:57.570
Yes, Ben.

31:57.708 --> 31:59.331
Yes!

31:59.469 --> 32:01.333
[Laughs]

32:01.471 --> 32:08.857
♪♪

32:08.996 --> 32:11.791
[Exhales deeply]

32:11.930 --> 32:13.932
Oh, my God.
This is amazing.

32:14.070 --> 32:15.588
You sure you want
to do this?

32:15.726 --> 32:16.900
Yes.

32:17.038 --> 32:19.523
I'm ready.

32:19.661 --> 32:21.525
Then let's get married
right now

32:21.663 --> 32:23.182
before you change
your mind.

32:23.320 --> 32:25.115
I'm not changing my --
What do you mean by now?

32:25.253 --> 32:27.014
Ah, it's been, like --

32:27.152 --> 32:29.326
Three -- Three times
a charm, right?

32:29.464 --> 32:31.673
Yes.

32:31.811 --> 32:34.918
I love you.

32:35.056 --> 32:36.920
I know.
I love you, too.

32:37.058 --> 32:39.474
♪♪

32:39.612 --> 32:41.028
[Cheering]

32:41.166 --> 32:43.202
[Laughs]

32:43.340 --> 32:45.549
Yay!

32:45.687 --> 32:48.518
Aww!

32:48.656 --> 32:50.589
[Applause]

32:50.727 --> 32:53.350
[Laughs]

32:53.488 --> 32:55.352
I still can't believe
Ben actually proposed

32:55.490 --> 32:56.871
to my mom behind our backs.

32:57.009 --> 32:59.563
My dad must be rolling
in his grave right now.

32:59.701 --> 33:01.393
You know, I feel like
she doesn't even realize

33:01.531 --> 33:04.361
he's only with her
because we're about to be rich.

33:04.499 --> 33:06.260
Right. Got to catch up on that.
Hang on.

33:06.398 --> 33:08.710
That's nothing but Nori.

33:08.848 --> 33:10.126
Nori: It's vow time.

33:10.264 --> 33:13.060
Oh, my God.
You look so beautiful.

33:13.198 --> 33:14.682
[Exhales deeply]

33:14.820 --> 33:16.028
We did it.

33:16.166 --> 33:19.169
[Indistinct conversation]

33:19.307 --> 33:21.068
Lionel: Ms. Duvernay?

33:21.206 --> 33:23.139
Ms. Duvernay?

33:23.277 --> 33:25.072
Actually, now it's Mrs. --

33:25.210 --> 33:27.074
Wait.
I recognize that voice.

33:27.212 --> 33:29.697
You're the executor.
What are you doing here?

33:29.835 --> 33:32.044
Are you following us?Ms. Duvernay?

33:32.182 --> 33:33.735
Duvernay-Cheatham.

33:33.873 --> 33:35.185
If you wish.

33:35.323 --> 33:38.257
I'm afraid time
is of the essence.

33:38.395 --> 33:41.191
I drove down from Atlanta
to expedite the execution

33:41.329 --> 33:43.849
of your grandfather's transfer
of estate.

33:43.987 --> 33:46.162
Well, what is the urgency?

33:46.300 --> 33:49.234
Your wedding, for one.

33:49.372 --> 33:53.859
Perhaps it's best I let
your grandfather explain.

33:53.997 --> 33:58.105
Papa Dean has left you
a series of legacy videos

33:58.243 --> 33:59.796
with specific instructions

33:59.934 --> 34:04.352
and guidance to guide you
in the managing of his estate.

34:04.490 --> 34:06.251
I'm staying
at the nearby Hilton.

34:06.389 --> 34:09.530
Meet me in conference room C
in one hour.

34:09.668 --> 34:11.187
Wait a second.
This is our --

34:11.324 --> 34:13.051
One hour.

34:13.188 --> 34:14.844
Ms. Duvernay.

34:14.983 --> 34:22.405
♪♪

34:25.960 --> 34:28.687
Ms. Duvernay.

34:28.824 --> 34:31.516
I'll wrap this up as quickly
as possible.

34:31.655 --> 34:34.175
It appears as if
your impromptu wedding

34:34.313 --> 34:36.418
has thrown a wrench

34:36.556 --> 34:40.456
into things
according to this arrangement.

34:40.594 --> 34:43.184
Is it possible that you
and I could speak alone?

34:43.322 --> 34:46.255
No.
Ben is -- is my husband,

34:46.393 --> 34:48.431
so whatever you wish
to say to me,

34:48.569 --> 34:50.295
you can say
in front of him.

34:50.433 --> 34:53.574
Very well.
I'll get right to it.

34:53.712 --> 34:55.955
Your grandfather,
the late, great

34:56.094 --> 35:00.684
Bishop Papa Dean has named you
the sole heir to his estate.

35:00.822 --> 35:02.721
Oh, my God.
We're going to be rich.

35:02.859 --> 35:06.932
His estate includes
several stock portfolios

35:07.070 --> 35:10.487
and an annuity valued
at $5 million.

35:10.625 --> 35:12.386
Your dividends
will be allocated

35:12.524 --> 35:15.803
via a monthly stipend
of $3,500.

35:15.941 --> 35:19.565
And furthermore,
your grandfather

35:19.703 --> 35:23.569
has left this for you
and your family.

35:25.053 --> 35:28.816
Oh, my God.
It's gorgeous.

35:30.576 --> 35:34.062
The property is
a 4,400-square-foot lake house

35:34.201 --> 35:36.375
with a lakefront view
and a dock.

